The paper deals with data stream algorithms and data structures for heavy hitters and related problems, which are typically studied in the subfield of data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). The use of Gaussian processes and other probabilistic techniques suggests a connection to machine learning and statistics (cs.LG), while the space complexity analysis and lower bounds are related to computational complexity (cs.CC) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
